info.name: Embeddings
info.description: ## Embeddings with the Gemini API The **Gemini API** supports several embedding models that generate vector representations (embeddings) for various input types‚Äîsuch as words, phrases, sentences, and even code. These embeddings can be used for a wide range of downstream tasks, including: - Semantic search - Text classification - Clustering - Information retrieval - Code search ...and more. üîó **Official Documentation**: [Embeddings API](https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/embeddings) --- ## üîç What Are Embeddings? **Embeddings** are numerical representations of input (e.g. text or code) in the form of high-dimensional vectors. These vectors capture **semantic meaning** and **contextual relationships** between inputs. - Text is converted into an array of floating-point numbers. - The length of this array is known as the **embedding dimensionality** (often hundreds of dimensions). - Inputs with similar meanings will produce **similar embeddings** (i.e., vectors that are "close" in vector space). > For example, the sentences `"I took my dog to the vet"` and `"I took my cat to the vet"` will yield embeddings that are close together, since they express similar ideas. --- ## ‚öôÔ∏è Task Types Task types help tailor the embeddings to specific downstream applications‚Äîimproving both **performance** and **cost-efficiency**. | Task Type | Description | | --- | --- | | `SEMANTIC_SIMILARITY` | Generate embeddings optimized for measuring the semantic similarity between texts. | | `CLASSIFICATION` | Generate embeddings suitable for classifying texts using preset labels. | | `CLUSTERING` | Produce embeddings that enable clustering of similar texts based on content. | | `RETRIEVAL_DOCUMENT`, `RETRIEVAL_QUERY`, `QUESTION_ANSWERING`, `FACT_VERIFICATION` | Generate embeddings optimized for information retrieval and search tasks. | | `CODE_RETRIEVAL_QUERY` | Designed to retrieve relevant code snippets based on natural language queries (e.g., ‚Äúsort an array‚Äù). Code embeddings use `RETRIEVAL_DOCUMENT`. | --- ## üß† Available Models The Gemini API currently provides multiple models for generating embeddings. For more information on each, see the official documentation: - [gemini-embedding-exp-03-07](https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models#gemini-embedding) - [text-embedding-004](https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models#text-embedding) - [embedding-001](https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models#text-embedding)
